WEBVTT

00:02.211 --> 00:06.875
JULIA: Chester's Mill is a place
like any other. At least it used to be.

00:07.049 --> 00:10.712
Until we were cut off from the rest
of the world by a mysterious dome.

00:13.138 --> 00:14.548
[M003

00:14.723 --> 00:18.762
J U L IA:
Invisible, indestructible, inescapable.

00:18.936 --> 00:20.767
We're trapped.

00:20.938 --> 00:23.429
JULIA: We don't know
where it came from or why it’s here,

00:23.607 --> 00:25.768
but now that we ’re all trapped
under the dome together,

00:25.943 --> 00:27.524
none of our secrets are safe.

00:28.195 --> 00:30.732
- I know, Junior.
- What are you talking about?

00:30.906 --> 00:32.271
About Angie.

00:32.866 --> 00:34.731
Hello?

00:37.246 --> 00:40.579
Nobody's gonna follow you
anywhere ever

00:40.749 --> 00:42.580
when they hear
just exactly who you are.

00:44.419 --> 00:46.876
The military plans
to launch a powerful missile

00:47.047 --> 00:48.457
in the hopes of destroying the dome.

00:48.632 --> 00:51.089
All right, everybody, stay put,
remain calm.

01:06.108 --> 01:08.099
JOE:
I can't believe it.

01:08.277 --> 01:10.063
The dome's still here.

01:10.237 --> 01:12.979
NORRIE: Good thing they evacuated
everyone outside.

01:18.745 --> 01:21.452
Hey, you guys okay?

01:21.623 --> 01:25.332
- We saw the missile hit the dome.
JOE: Didn't even put a dent in it.

01:25.836 --> 01:28.999
NORRIE: What's it made of
if a bomb couldn't blow it up?

01:29.172 --> 01:32.710
She's right. How is that possible?

01:32.884 --> 01:35.341
I don't know. Nothing about this thing
makes any sense.

01:35.512 --> 01:38.925
You can say that again.
Still smooth as a baby's butt.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.886
Stay back. Stay back, everyone.

01:42.060 --> 01:44.096
Remember Sheriff Perkins?

01:44.271 --> 01:46.637
Touching that thing
exploded his damn pacemaker.

01:46.815 --> 01:47.850
Norrie!

01:48.817 --> 01:50.523
NORRIE:
Mom!

01:51.903 --> 01:55.987
- Oh, God, are you okay?
NORRIE: I'm sorry I ran off.

01:56.158 --> 01:58.023
If anything had happened to you...

02:00.162 --> 02:02.118
JIM:
Linda, where are your deputies?

02:02.289 --> 02:04.951
Who do you think I'm trying to find?
Have you seen Junior?

02:05.125 --> 02:07.161
He didn't evacuate to the factory
with everyone else.

02:07.336 --> 02:09.543
Yeah, I know,
I've been looking for him myself.

02:09.713 --> 02:11.669
But he's a big boy.
He can handle himself.

02:11.840 --> 02:14.172
Yeah, well, I can't say the same
about Reverend Coggins.

02:14.343 --> 02:17.380
Carter found his body by the dome
where we had Visitors' Day.

02:18.847 --> 02:20.838
Good Lord.

02:21.016 --> 02:23.632
- Coggins is dead?
LINDA: His hearing aid exploded.

02:23.810 --> 02:26.187
He must have touched the dome
and itjust fried him.

02:27.314 --> 02:29.646
OLLIE:
First Duke, now the Reverend?

02:29.816 --> 02:31.681
How many more of us
is this thing gonna kill?

02:31.860 --> 02:34.021
Just take it easy, Ollie.
You're scaring people, okay?

02:34.196 --> 02:37.359
It's a little too late for that now. We've
got a right to know what's going on.

02:37.532 --> 02:40.023
We've all banded together before
and we survived, okay?

02:40.202 --> 02:43.069
- Yeah, until we run out of food in here.
- How about electricity?

02:43.246 --> 02:45.783
- I'm nearly out of propane.
- Hell, I ran out yesterday.

02:45.957 --> 02:48.369
Been warming up canned soup
in my fireplace.

02:48.543 --> 02:50.704
I suggest we take this
to a town-hall meeting. We can--

02:50.879 --> 02:53.416
What, so you can keep jawing
while more people die?

02:53.590 --> 02:55.672
Hey, myjawing's gotten us
through plenty, Ollie.

02:55.842 --> 02:58.049
Why don't you help by keeping
your damn head on straight?

02:58.220 --> 03:00.256
Can we please just get out of here?

03:00.430 --> 03:02.546
Yeah, before a fight breaks out.

03:02.724 --> 03:07.138
- It's like a hundred degrees today.
- Let's get back to the car.

03:07.312 --> 03:08.848
Joe, you can come with us.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.183
Honestly, I'm a little scared.

03:16.947 --> 03:19.609
What happens when
we run out of everything?

03:20.409 --> 03:22.525
What do we do then?

03:24.621 --> 03:26.577
I don't know.

03:27.582 --> 03:29.618
[STATIC SCREECHING
OVER RADIO]

03:31.211 --> 03:33.327
The walkies aren't working.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.626
I can't get a frequency.

03:37.551 --> 03:41.294
Hey, Barbie,
till I can reach my deputies,

03:42.222 --> 03:43.587
I'm gonna need another hand.

03:46.226 --> 03:49.718
I'll help you,
but I don't need your badge.

03:52.065 --> 03:55.603
Come on, I'll give you a lift into town.
We can talk about how this will work.

03:55.777 --> 03:57.938
I'm gonna head over
to the radio station.

03:58.113 --> 04:00.445
See if they're picking anything up
from the outside.

04:01.783 --> 04:05.275
- I'll see you later?
- Yeah, okay.

04:05.454 --> 04:08.366
OLLIE: You know what this means,
folks. We're never getting out of here.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.781
ANDREA: Ollie, at least
you have a farm to feed yourself.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.460
What about the rest of us?

04:12.627 --> 04:14.458
JIM:
You have my word, people.

04:14.629 --> 04:17.120
No one's gonna starve
in Chester's Mill.

04:22.471 --> 04:24.883
It's crazy.

04:25.056 --> 04:27.342
Five minutes ago,
I thought we were gonna die.

04:30.771 --> 04:33.808
It's worse not knowing what's next.

04:33.982 --> 04:36.849
You don't need to be scared, Angie.

04:38.945 --> 04:41.482
Didn't you notice I'm a deputy now?

04:42.699 --> 04:47.443
People trust me, just like you should.

04:49.539 --> 04:53.282
Whatever happens,
I'll take care of you.

04:58.340 --> 04:59.455
[JUNIOR GRUNTING]

05:01.885 --> 05:06.049
Angie, don't do this! Angie! Angie!

05:06.223 --> 05:09.841
ALICE: Just let me out of the car.
Let me out of the car.

05:11.686 --> 05:14.098
Why'd you make me stop?
What's wrong?

05:14.272 --> 05:18.390
Ijust-- I need some air.
It's boiling hot in there.

05:18.568 --> 05:20.479
- Mom, are you okay?
- She's fine.

05:20.654 --> 05:24.272
Alice, just get back in the car.
I'll blast the ac.

05:24.449 --> 05:27.657
ALICE: What time's our flight?
- What flight?

05:27.828 --> 05:31.320
- To LA. I don't wanna miss it.
NORRIE: Mom, watch out!

05:31.498 --> 05:33.363
[HORN HONKING]

05:33.542 --> 05:35.032
NORRIE:
Mom!

05:49.432 --> 05:50.763
Oh, my God.

05:53.562 --> 05:55.177
JOE:
Hurry.

05:58.066 --> 06:00.603
- Go, go, grab him!
JOE: I've got you.

06:00.777 --> 06:02.358
NORRIE:
We're gonna get you out, okay?

06:02.529 --> 06:04.235
Help me get him out.

06:27.345 --> 06:29.336
[SIREN WAILS]

06:32.934 --> 06:36.222
LINDA:
Everybody okay? What happened?

06:36.396 --> 06:39.229
Alice didn't see the truck coming.
The driver swerved and hit the tower.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.105
Joe and Norrie
pulled him outjust in time.

06:41.276 --> 06:44.609
Okay, got him. Good job, you guys.

06:48.783 --> 06:50.910
The pipe's a goner.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.034
Where's your tower
get its water from?

06:53.204 --> 06:56.412
Lake Eastpointe.
It's our main source.

06:56.583 --> 06:57.914
Well, we'll haul water from there.

06:58.084 --> 07:00.496
In the meantime,
we should check it out.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.334
Okay, look at me, look at me.

07:05.508 --> 07:07.885
Alice, when's the last time
you took your insulin?

07:08.053 --> 07:11.921
I ran out. With the bomb craziness
and everything, Ijust...

07:12.098 --> 07:13.258
I lost track.

07:13.433 --> 07:16.015
Come on, we're gonna get you
to the clinic right now.

07:19.147 --> 07:22.435
- What's wrong with your mom?
- She's a diabetic.

07:22.609 --> 07:25.316
Kind of loses it
when she forgets to take her insulin.

07:25.487 --> 07:27.478
[STATIC CRACKLING]

07:28.823 --> 07:30.074
[SIGHS]

07:30.825 --> 07:31.860
[STATIC SCREECHING]

07:32.035 --> 07:33.400
What is that noise?

07:33.578 --> 07:35.660
I don't know,
but it's jamming our broadcast.

07:35.830 --> 07:37.491
Kind of sounds
like the alien from Aliens.

07:37.666 --> 07:40.624
JULIE: Well, all the police walkies
are making the same sound.

07:40.794 --> 07:43.786
ls Dodee picking up any military
chatter from outside the dome?

07:44.798 --> 07:46.038
Screech is jamming that too.

07:46.216 --> 07:50.129
And if it's this loud,
then the source is probably close.

07:50.303 --> 07:53.670
- How close?
- Best guess? Mile or two.

07:53.848 --> 07:56.339
So it's inside Chester's Mill?

07:57.394 --> 08:00.181
[BOTH SIGH]

08:00.355 --> 08:02.687
Listen, if it's that close,
maybe we can find it.

08:02.857 --> 08:04.848
DODEE:
One step ahead of you, Julia.

08:05.026 --> 08:07.017
[YAGI BEEPING]

08:08.697 --> 08:10.983
Do I even wanna know what that is?

08:11.157 --> 08:12.943
Us radio heads call it a yagi.

08:13.118 --> 08:14.949
I rigged it to locate the source
of the screech

08:15.120 --> 08:17.577
using frequency triangulation.

08:17.747 --> 08:20.659
Look, whatever this screech is,
it can't be a coincidence

08:20.834 --> 08:24.167
that it started just as the missile
was about to hit the dome.

08:24.337 --> 08:26.043
You think the dome
was trying to scream?

08:26.214 --> 08:28.671
- Or protect itself.
DODEE: Who knows?

08:28.842 --> 08:32.084
But if it was, it might be
what's generating the dome itself.

08:32.262 --> 08:35.720
We just have to follow the signal
to the power source.

08:35.890 --> 08:39.553
Well, if that's true,
then if we can track it down...

08:39.728 --> 08:42.185
Maybe we can turn it off.

08:45.108 --> 08:49.898
It's none of my business,
but you're lucky to have her.

08:50.071 --> 08:51.777
Her?

08:51.948 --> 08:53.904
I have eyes, you know.

08:54.075 --> 08:57.033
Oh, Julia and I aren't exactly an item.

08:57.203 --> 09:01.412
Well, from the sparks
that I saw flying, you should be.

09:02.417 --> 09:05.534
I'd kill to have Rusty back right now.

09:05.712 --> 09:09.250
- How long you two been together?
- Three years.

09:09.424 --> 09:11.130
We're supposed to get married
next month.

09:11.301 --> 09:14.418
But now itjust seems like
some dream I made up.

09:19.976 --> 09:21.557
What the hell?

09:30.820 --> 09:33.903
You shouldn't be out.
I was just here the other day.

09:34.074 --> 09:35.564
You had insulin.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.949
ADAMS:
We have 23 diabetics in Chester's Mill.

09:38.119 --> 09:41.236
Our insulin supply is gone.

09:41.706 --> 09:43.321
Pharmacy has to have some.

09:43.708 --> 09:45.369
When Reverend Coggins
ransacked the place,

09:45.543 --> 09:48.250
he took all of the drugs,
including the insulin.

09:50.298 --> 09:53.040
What are we supposed to do?

09:55.678 --> 09:57.214
ADAMS:
Pray.

10:02.560 --> 10:04.346
Jim, we have a situation.

10:04.521 --> 10:06.352
- The water tower--
JIM: Yeah, I know, it fell.

10:06.523 --> 10:09.139
We'll just have to get our water
from Lake Eastpointe.

10:09.317 --> 10:10.818
Can't.

10:14.322 --> 10:15.653
What are you doing?

10:23.164 --> 10:26.281
This is the water from the lake.
It's polluted with methane.

10:26.459 --> 10:28.415
Must've cut through
an underground mineral pocket

10:28.586 --> 10:29.871
when the dome came down.

10:30.296 --> 10:31.376
So it's undrinkable.

10:31.881 --> 10:33.667
Yeah, until we figure out
how to filter it.

10:33.842 --> 10:36.299
What about rain?

10:36.469 --> 10:38.846
Is that dome high enough
for storm clouds to form?

10:39.013 --> 10:40.628
I have no idea.

10:41.933 --> 10:46.472
You know, not too many people take
the time to get to know their town.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.352
A shame, really.

10:48.523 --> 10:50.059
There's history here.

10:50.233 --> 10:52.565
Right in our own backyards.

10:52.735 --> 10:55.568
My grandfather gave me this map
when I was a kid.

10:55.738 --> 11:00.323
I used to spend hours poring over it,
learning the lay of the land.

11:00.493 --> 11:03.280
There are artesian wells
underneath Chester's Mill.

11:03.454 --> 11:06.491
Now, some have dried up by now,

11:06.666 --> 11:09.874
but this one here
is still flowing strongly.

11:10.044 --> 11:13.002
It's right under
Ollie Densmore's place.

11:13.173 --> 11:15.209
And I'm guessing he owns the rights.

11:15.383 --> 11:16.839
- We have to go see him.
JIM: No, no.

11:17.010 --> 11:20.377
I've known Ollie long enough to know
that he can be a pain in the ass,

11:20.555 --> 11:22.967
so I'll go talk to him.

11:33.693 --> 11:34.728
JUNIOR:
Dad.

11:35.904 --> 11:37.394
Where you been? You okay?

11:37.572 --> 11:39.312
I can't find Angie.

11:39.490 --> 11:40.991
- She's gone.
- Was she with you

11:41.159 --> 11:44.868
- when the bomb went off?
- Yeah, but she got away.

11:45.038 --> 11:46.073
Well, then find her.

11:46.247 --> 11:48.738
If she opens her mouth
about being locked up...

11:49.250 --> 11:50.956
Now, I've been looking for her.

11:51.669 --> 11:53.705
Besides, you're the one
who let her go.

11:53.880 --> 11:55.791
Damn it, don't you put this
on me, Junior.

11:55.965 --> 11:57.375
This is your mess.

11:57.550 --> 12:00.132
And right now I got one of my own,
so for once in your life,

12:00.303 --> 12:02.760
do your own damage control.
Get out there and find that girl.

12:10.063 --> 12:13.271
BARBIE: Hey, so how long
has Big Jim known Ollie Densmore?

12:13.441 --> 12:15.602
LINDA:
The way Duke told it, all their lives.

12:15.777 --> 12:19.065
Jim and Ollie would be friends one day
and then enemies the next.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.525
They'd patch it up over a burger,

12:21.699 --> 12:24.281
but they'd be fighting about
something new the following week.

12:24.452 --> 12:27.444
And speaking of fighting,
we should probably check this out.

12:27.622 --> 12:29.453
[ALL CHATTERING]

12:31.793 --> 12:33.124
TERRY:
Folks, listen, I'm sorry,

12:33.294 --> 12:36.661
but the only payment I can accept
is either propane or batteries.

12:36.839 --> 12:39.455
So our money's no good now?
I mean, we got cash.

12:39.634 --> 12:41.966
And we've been waiting
out here forever.

12:42.136 --> 12:44.127
Terry, what's going on here?

12:44.973 --> 12:47.305
I'm just trying to explain
the new reality to these people.

12:47.976 --> 12:51.059
Look, I can't feed my family
with money no one's gonna take.

12:51.229 --> 12:52.264
DRES:
New reality?

12:52.730 --> 12:54.686
- Sounds like a scam to me.
- I'm not trying to--

12:54.857 --> 12:58.145
- Hey, come on, guys, come on.
ANDREA: Is it true the lake is ruined?

12:58.319 --> 13:00.856
- I hear we're gonna run out of water.
- If we haven't already.

13:01.030 --> 13:02.770
Starting a panic
is not gonna help anyone.

13:02.949 --> 13:06.942
All right? So does anybody here have
batteries that we can loan to Dres?

13:07.120 --> 13:08.735
Anybody?

13:11.416 --> 13:13.452
Thank you.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.662
There's no need for alarm.

13:15.837 --> 13:17.327
I'm sorry for making a scene.

13:18.006 --> 13:19.837
Thank you, sheriff.

13:20.675 --> 13:22.961
You really believe that?
No need for alarm?

13:23.136 --> 13:24.546
Rule number one
of law enforcement:

13:24.721 --> 13:26.928
You always believe in
the goodness of people you serve.

13:27.098 --> 13:29.339
That's what Duke taught me
on the first day of the job.

13:29.517 --> 13:33.726
- Yeah, and if they prove you wrong?
- Rule number two:

13:36.774 --> 13:38.810
You do what you gotta do.

13:39.235 --> 13:42.398
- That's not a good idea.
- Why?

13:43.364 --> 13:44.524
I mean, didn't you have a gun

13:44.699 --> 13:48.237
- when you chased after Randolph?
- Yeah, but Randolph killed Freddy.

13:48.411 --> 13:50.276
These people...

13:52.206 --> 13:53.582
These people are scared.

13:58.421 --> 14:03.256
To tell you the truth, so am I.

14:08.181 --> 14:11.218
JIM:
Ollie! Hey!

14:11.392 --> 14:13.053
I won't take up too much
of your time.

14:13.227 --> 14:15.354
All the time in the world
for you, Big Jim.

14:15.897 --> 14:20.436
- We got a water problem.
- That concerns me, uh, how?

14:20.610 --> 14:21.850
You got a well,

14:22.028 --> 14:25.020
and the people of Chester's Mill
could really use your help.

14:30.953 --> 14:34.741
That's typical. You always
take me for granted, Jim.

14:34.916 --> 14:36.247
All us farmers.

14:36.667 --> 14:37.702
Till now.

14:37.877 --> 14:41.085
You still sore the town council took Kip
Lester's side on that fence dispute?

14:41.255 --> 14:44.873
That so-called fence dispute
lost me seven acres of my farm.

14:45.051 --> 14:46.632
It was 15 years ago, Ollie.

14:46.803 --> 14:49.920
That's a drop in the bucket compared
to how long you and me go back.

14:50.098 --> 14:52.054
I figured I could've counted on you.

14:52.225 --> 14:53.931
You know the law
tied my hands on that.

14:54.102 --> 14:56.058
Like that's stopped you before now.

14:56.229 --> 14:59.096
- Damn it, be reasonable, Ollie.
- That's exactly what I'm being.

14:59.273 --> 15:03.141
You want my water,
you'll have to pay for it.

15:04.737 --> 15:08.355
Today at the dome, you were talking
about running low on propane.

15:08.533 --> 15:09.989
You know, the propane it takes

15:10.159 --> 15:12.536
to run your irrigation system
and light your house.

15:12.703 --> 15:15.911
Let me guess. You have some.

15:16.082 --> 15:17.117
- Plenty.
- Heh.

15:17.291 --> 15:20.419
Why am I not surprised
Big Jim Rennie just happens to have

15:20.586 --> 15:23.419
what Chester's Mill needs
in its moment of crisis?

15:23.589 --> 15:24.920
It's nothing sinister, Ollie.

15:25.091 --> 15:27.753
Town keeps a reserve
in case of emergency.

15:27.927 --> 15:29.292
[ENGINE STARTS]

15:29.470 --> 15:32.507
You get me propane,
town gets its water.

15:49.615 --> 15:51.731
CARTER: Just in time.
- Things getting out of control?

15:51.909 --> 15:53.319
Not yet, but the mood's pretty ugly.

15:53.494 --> 15:55.485
Barbie, get inside
and keep peace at the register.

15:55.663 --> 15:58.154
Carter, slow the flow
of people going inside.

16:01.002 --> 16:03.243
Junior, where have you been
all morning?

16:03.421 --> 16:06.333
Sorry, Linda, I got a situation
I need to take care of.

16:06.507 --> 16:08.998
- I'm looking for someone.
- Well, I need you to do yourjob.

16:11.637 --> 16:13.343
Ladies and gentlemen,
due to demand,

16:13.514 --> 16:16.221
we are now limiting
each customer's purchase

16:16.392 --> 16:18.633
to a total of two liters of water.

16:18.811 --> 16:22.395
Work the aisles.
Just keep smiling and stay alert.

16:26.027 --> 16:28.518
JUNIOR:
Waylon, Clint, put it back.

16:30.490 --> 16:32.902
Well, isn't this cute?
Little Big Jim playing cop.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.408
- Drop those and step back.
- Or what?

16:35.578 --> 16:38.411
- You gonna teach us a lesson?
- Ifl have to.

16:39.165 --> 16:41.030
Hey, come on. Are you serious?

16:41.209 --> 16:42.699
IDA:
Hey! I was here first!

16:42.877 --> 16:44.663
- My son is sick. I need this!
- I don't care!

16:44.837 --> 16:48.204
Hey, hey, come on, ladies.
Hey, knock it off. Knock it off.

16:49.550 --> 16:51.051
NORRIE:
Joe, what am I gonna do?

16:52.053 --> 16:55.045
I can'tjust let my mom die.

16:56.307 --> 16:58.263
Not like this.

16:58.434 --> 17:01.096
Tell me how to help.

17:01.646 --> 17:03.887
I'll do anything.

17:06.734 --> 17:07.849
Where are you going?

17:08.027 --> 17:10.143
Nurse said there's a bunch
of other diabetics in town.

17:10.321 --> 17:11.902
Their files have to
be in here somewhere.

17:12.073 --> 17:14.485
You think people will just give you
their insulin if you ask?

17:14.659 --> 17:15.990
Who said I was gonna ask?

17:16.160 --> 17:19.072
- Norrie--
- If you don't like it, don't come.

17:19.872 --> 17:21.533
JULIA:
Are we getting closer to the Signal?

17:22.625 --> 17:24.081
DODEE:
No.

17:24.252 --> 17:26.083
What?

17:26.254 --> 17:27.915
Our source, all of a sudden,
it's moving.

17:28.422 --> 17:31.585
- What kind of a power source moves?
- I'm not sure.

17:33.761 --> 17:37.970
All right, well,
let's see if we can home in on it.

17:42.770 --> 17:44.761
[CROWD SHOUTING]

17:46.065 --> 17:47.100
Carter!

17:49.318 --> 17:51.934
Hold it, hold it. What do we got?

17:54.448 --> 17:56.985
No,no,no.

17:57.493 --> 18:00.951
- Angie, where have you been?
- Oh. Rose.

18:02.123 --> 18:04.159
ROSE:
Are you okay?

18:06.127 --> 18:08.118
Junior, he...

18:10.089 --> 18:12.580
What? Junior what?

18:14.176 --> 18:18.636
The day that the dome came down,
Junior locked me in his fallout shelter.

18:18.806 --> 18:22.640
- What?
- I tried to escape, but I couldn't.

18:22.810 --> 18:25.893
- And then Big Jim found me.
- And he let you out.

18:26.063 --> 18:29.976
- No, he locked me in again.
- Big Jim did?

18:30.151 --> 18:32.642
And the only reason he let me out
this morning is because

18:33.487 --> 18:35.864
he thought this missile
was gonna kill us all.

18:36.032 --> 18:38.774
I can't believe Big Jim would do
something like that.

18:38.951 --> 18:40.327
Rose, I'm not lying.

18:41.120 --> 18:45.329
When he finally let me out, I ran.

18:45.499 --> 18:49.037
And ran and I ran
to my parents' house.

18:49.211 --> 18:51.372
- I couldn't find Joe.
- Oh.

18:51.547 --> 18:53.458
- I couldn't find my brother.
- Oh.

18:53.633 --> 18:57.626
Your brother is safe and so are you.

19:02.391 --> 19:04.848
But Junior's a cop now.

19:05.019 --> 19:07.476
And his dad's a councilman.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.559
Who's gonna believe my word
against theirs?

19:12.902 --> 19:14.688
I do.

19:15.196 --> 19:16.311
I do.

19:17.531 --> 19:19.032
Don't you worry, honey.

19:19.200 --> 19:22.237
We'll make sure
that everybody else does too.

19:22.745 --> 19:25.953
- Are you sure a diabetic lives here?
- Yeah.

19:26.123 --> 19:28.159
Name's on the medical files I pulled.

19:28.334 --> 19:33.044
Ray Garcia, 341 Cupidas Drive.

19:33.214 --> 19:36.627
Yeah, well, no one's home.
Can we come back later?

19:36.801 --> 19:39.292
Joe, we don't want them to be home.

19:39.470 --> 19:42.382
Plus maybe they got caught
outside the dome.

19:54.110 --> 19:56.021
Wait, wait, Norrie, we can'tjust--

20:04.161 --> 20:05.276
[GUN COCKS]

20:08.249 --> 20:09.534
What are you kids doing?

20:09.709 --> 20:11.665
My mom needs insulin.

20:11.836 --> 20:13.792
RAY:
So you figured you'd steal mine?

20:14.422 --> 20:17.585
She'S-- She's gonna die.

20:18.259 --> 20:20.716
Just like the rest of us.

20:21.971 --> 20:24.758
I took my last dose yesterday.

20:28.227 --> 20:33.267
Now go on, get out of here
before I blow your damn heads off.

20:39.989 --> 20:42.150
[CROWD SHOUTING]

20:42.324 --> 20:43.404
Back up! Move!

20:47.455 --> 20:50.117
No,no,no!

20:54.503 --> 20:55.788
Stop! Let her go!

20:55.963 --> 20:57.373
- No!
- Get your hands off me!

20:57.548 --> 20:59.504
BARBIE:
Get your hands off of her.

21:00.176 --> 21:02.087
MAN:
GO to hell!

21:04.638 --> 21:06.378
BARBIE:
Out of the way. Move it! Move!

21:18.486 --> 21:20.442
[BOTH GRUNTING]

21:31.123 --> 21:32.988
LINDA:
Barbie.

21:33.167 --> 21:35.658
Barbie, get ahold Of yourself.

21:40.382 --> 21:42.998
Can I count on you?

21:43.177 --> 21:45.509
It won't happen again.

21:46.013 --> 21:48.880
This thing iS starting to Spread.
We need to do something and fast.

21:49.058 --> 21:50.548
Carter, come with me.

22:04.824 --> 22:06.405
[GLASS SHATTERING]

22:12.915 --> 22:14.826
What the hell do you think
you're doing?

22:15.000 --> 22:17.207
We know that you still got meat
in that freezer of yours.

22:17.378 --> 22:18.413
ROSE:
Yeah.

22:19.046 --> 22:21.378
And it doesn't belong
to either Of you.

22:21.549 --> 22:24.962
You don't get it, Rose.
We're stuck in here with no water.

22:25.135 --> 22:26.545
FOOd'S running out.

22:26.720 --> 22:29.553
A bomb couldn't even crack
that damn thing.

22:29.890 --> 22:31.596
So we're just gonna take
what we want.

22:32.268 --> 22:35.135
ANGIE: Aah!
- Right after you kiss my ass!

22:35.604 --> 22:37.720
[ANGIE SCREAMING]

22:37.898 --> 22:39.183
[ROSE GRUNTING]

22:47.908 --> 22:50.741
No! Rose!

22:52.329 --> 22:56.413
You bastard! Aah!

23:17.813 --> 23:19.599
[SIREN WAILING]

23:19.773 --> 23:21.764
[CROWD SHOUTING]

23:24.778 --> 23:26.769
JUNIOR: Where have you been?
LINDA: At the station.

23:26.947 --> 23:28.858
I remembered Duke telling me
about some riot gear

23:29.033 --> 23:30.773
the feds sent us after 9/11.

23:30.951 --> 23:35.945
This is it? This stuff is--
It's ten years old. It loses effectiveness.

23:36.123 --> 23:37.909
Get ready to Clear the crowd.

23:43.756 --> 23:46.247
[CROWD SHOUTING]

23:51.472 --> 23:52.757
BARBIE:
Tear gas isn't working.

24:00.522 --> 24:02.023
DODEE:
Slow down, Slow down.

24:02.733 --> 24:04.064
- Damn it!
- Now What?

24:04.234 --> 24:06.225
DODEE:
I lost the Signal.

24:06.904 --> 24:10.817
- How?
- I don't know, just give me a second.

24:10.991 --> 24:12.822
Wait, wait, wait, it's back.
Hurry, hurry, go.

24:12.993 --> 24:14.984
JULIA: Okay, all right.
- We're Close.

24:18.290 --> 24:22.454
The door's unlocked.
It's not like we're breaking in.

24:22.628 --> 24:25.085
JOE:
Now say it like you mean it.

24:40.354 --> 24:41.639
Nore?

24:46.068 --> 24:47.729
What are you doing here?

24:47.903 --> 24:50.690
We werejust, um...

24:52.783 --> 24:56.025
- Where are your parents?
- Mom went to the store.

24:56.203 --> 24:59.036
Dad can't get back home
With that dome thing outside.

25:04.336 --> 25:06.247
We're not gonna hurt you.

25:06.714 --> 25:09.046
I'm not scared.

25:09.216 --> 25:11.707
Mom says
I'm not a little boy anymore.

25:11.885 --> 25:14.376
I even do my own Shots now.

25:17.558 --> 25:20.891
- You have diabetes?
- Yeah, but it's not a big deal.

25:26.275 --> 25:28.891
Take these back to the fridge.

25:33.240 --> 25:34.821
Wait.

25:41.206 --> 25:43.743
KAY:
What the hell are you doing here?

25:43.917 --> 25:45.532
Get out.

25:48.422 --> 25:50.413
I'm sorry.

25:51.467 --> 25:54.550
It was a stupid idea. You were right.

25:54.720 --> 25:57.302
Let's just go back to your mom's.

25:57.931 --> 25:59.057
JULIA:
Hey, Joe.

25:59.224 --> 26:00.930
What are you guys doing here?

26:01.101 --> 26:04.593
- Uh, we werejust...
- Out on a walk.

26:04.772 --> 26:06.103
What are you guys doing?

26:06.690 --> 26:08.521
- Wild-goose hunt.
- Not anymore.

26:08.692 --> 26:10.432
The signal's coming from right here.

26:10.611 --> 26:11.817
[BEEPING]

26:12.237 --> 26:13.272
From this house?

26:15.365 --> 26:17.105
I think it's coming from them.

26:22.831 --> 26:24.696
OLLIE:
What's this?

26:25.626 --> 26:27.491
It's my end of the deal.

26:29.463 --> 26:31.124
Got What you want, Ollie.

26:32.883 --> 26:36.296
So be prepared for townfolk to start
coming over and getting their water.

26:36.470 --> 26:37.755
[OLLIE CHUCKLES]

26:37.930 --> 26:40.342
Well, it's a good start, anyway.

26:40.724 --> 26:43.261
Need another delivery
about a week from now.

26:43.435 --> 26:45.016
You know, I could always
seize that well,

26:45.187 --> 26:46.427
you backwoods son of a bitch.

26:46.605 --> 26:50.564
And I'm sure you'd find some bylaw
or loophole to justify doing it.

26:50.734 --> 26:53.476
I mean, that's always been
the Big Jim way, hasn't it?

26:53.654 --> 26:55.986
- But not anymore.
- What's that supposed to mean?

26:56.156 --> 26:59.444
It means I don't give a rat's ass What
piece of official paper you pull out.

26:59.618 --> 27:02.200
You step foot on my land
except to bring me more propane,

27:02.371 --> 27:04.157
you'll get a bullet between the eyes.

27:04.873 --> 27:07.990
I always could Shoot better than you.

27:09.503 --> 27:10.788
JIM:
Be careful, Ollie.

27:11.505 --> 27:14.463
Times like this,
you don't wanna stand alone.

27:16.844 --> 27:20.507
Cross me.
We'll see Who stands Where.

27:26.854 --> 27:27.889
[CLINT SNICKERS]

27:28.063 --> 27:30.896
Yeah, Junior's girl really
put up a fight.

27:31.066 --> 27:33.182
She can't now.

27:36.238 --> 27:38.524
GO watch the door, Clint.

27:40.617 --> 27:43.450
Angie MCAIister.

27:43.620 --> 27:46.202
I don't think you're gonna mind.

27:59.720 --> 28:01.506
JOE:
Wait, this is our fault?

28:01.680 --> 28:04.547
So you think we're What's jamming
all the frequencies in town?

28:04.725 --> 28:07.091
All we know is,
Whatever this Signal thing is,

28:07.269 --> 28:10.227
it started today
and it led us straight to you guys.

28:10.397 --> 28:13.889
Yeah, but why today?
I mean, it's not like we did anything.

28:14.067 --> 28:16.524
- I know it doesn't make any sense.
- It sort of does.

28:18.238 --> 28:21.571
- We have to tell someone.
JULIA: Tell us What?

28:22.201 --> 28:26.740
The day the dome came down,
we both started having seizures.

28:26.914 --> 28:31.874
All the people who've seen uS seize
have said that we said something.

28:32.044 --> 28:33.409
The exact same thing.

28:34.254 --> 28:37.746
- Okay, I'm officially freaked out.
- Here.

28:44.014 --> 28:48.599
JOE: Pink stars are falling in lines.
NORRIE: Pink stars are falling.

28:48.769 --> 28:51.055
- Pink stars are falling.
- Pink stars are falling.

28:51.230 --> 28:55.394
- Pink stars are falling in lines.
- Pink stars are falling in lines.

28:55.567 --> 28:58.934
- Pink stars are falling...
- Pink stars are falling...

28:59.112 --> 29:00.773
[BOTH GRUNTING]

29:01.907 --> 29:03.522
BARBIE:
Hey, break it up!

29:09.706 --> 29:11.822
Sorry, man, diner's Closed.

29:12.793 --> 29:15.125
When did Rose
make you the doorman?

29:15.295 --> 29:16.375
- Rose?
BARBIE: Yeah.

29:16.546 --> 29:18.411
Waylon, get out of there!

29:25.389 --> 29:26.629
Hey!

29:29.810 --> 29:31.516
[BOTH GRUNTING]

29:47.202 --> 29:49.193
[WAYLON COUGHING]

29:57.504 --> 29:58.869
What happened?

30:00.674 --> 30:02.005
Rose is dead.

30:02.175 --> 30:03.631
Angie's got a nasty bump
on her head.

30:03.802 --> 30:05.303
Rose?

30:05.804 --> 30:07.886
- Oh, my God.
- I need your keys.

30:08.056 --> 30:10.217
I gotta get her to the Clinic.

30:15.856 --> 30:17.016
LINDA:
Damn it.

30:17.190 --> 30:18.976
Someone Slashed the tires.

30:23.238 --> 30:25.604
It's time for rule number two.

30:27.868 --> 30:30.154
Stop. Stop!

30:46.720 --> 30:48.711
[HORN HONKING]

30:48.889 --> 30:50.049
MAN:
It can rain!

30:50.223 --> 30:51.963
It can rain inside the dome!

30:52.142 --> 30:53.882
[CHEERS]

30:54.061 --> 30:56.973
It's rain! Came out of nowhere!
All right!

30:57.147 --> 31:00.230
Don't just stand there, folks.
Grab a bucket, grab a trash can!

31:00.400 --> 31:02.937
We need to save every drop we can!
Now, come on!

31:13.080 --> 31:15.241
Hey, I gotta get her to the Clinic.
Can you take her?

31:15.415 --> 31:19.579
Of course! IS that Angie MCAIister?
What happened?

31:19.753 --> 31:22.415
LooterS. They broke in to the diner.
They knocked her out.

31:24.591 --> 31:26.422
And Rose...

31:27.469 --> 31:28.959
What about Rose?

31:29.846 --> 31:31.052
She's dead.

31:33.767 --> 31:37.555
Two guys. One kept calling
the other one Waylon?

31:37.729 --> 31:39.765
Sounds like the Dundee brothers.

31:48.407 --> 31:49.567
Find them.

31:49.741 --> 31:51.197
[ENGINE STARTS]

32:12.848 --> 32:15.134
JOE:
Dome's still here.

32:16.101 --> 32:18.342
Outside it's totally dry.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.636
How is it only raining in here?

32:20.814 --> 32:22.930
The dome must have
its own microclimate.

32:23.108 --> 32:27.693
The water from the lake evaporates,
but the dome traps it inside.

32:27.863 --> 32:30.650
But the beautiful thing about
the evaporation process

32:30.824 --> 32:33.657
iS it filters the water
so you can drink it.

32:33.827 --> 32:36.409
Guess we're not gonna run out
of water after all.

32:36.580 --> 32:38.161
Yeah, great.

32:38.331 --> 32:41.789
So now we can spend the rest
of our liveS inside this damn thing.

32:44.504 --> 32:45.835
Whoa.

32:46.631 --> 32:48.713
[MELLOW POP MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO]

32:50.677 --> 32:54.795
Radio's working again. Whatever
was jamming the airwaves is gone.

32:59.019 --> 33:01.852
It's because Joe and Norrie
touched the dome together.

33:03.064 --> 33:05.020
What the hell does that mean?

33:05.192 --> 33:06.227
Don't look at me.

33:06.401 --> 33:08.016
You know What?
I don't have time for this.

33:08.195 --> 33:10.026
- I've gotta get to my mom.
- I'll drive you.

33:10.197 --> 33:12.984
No, the Clinic's not far. I'll walk.

33:13.158 --> 33:14.568
You come With.

33:24.002 --> 33:26.288
They're connected to it.

33:26.463 --> 33:30.832
It's like the dome is using them.

33:32.302 --> 33:34.213
Okay.

33:34.846 --> 33:37.223
- How?
- I don't know yet.

33:38.725 --> 33:41.216
We could have died today
in that missile strike.

33:41.394 --> 33:44.682
And instead,
the dome ended up protecting us.

33:44.856 --> 33:48.565
And just when we need water,
it rains.

33:49.611 --> 33:51.567
I mean, this can't
just be a coincidence.

33:51.738 --> 33:54.445
Okay, so, what,
now the dome's helping us?

33:54.616 --> 33:56.572
Maybe.

34:00.622 --> 34:05.116
Maybe it's trying to reassure us.

34:05.919 --> 34:08.331
First it traps us.

34:08.505 --> 34:11.087
Now it's trying to reassure us.

34:11.925 --> 34:13.415
No.

34:13.593 --> 34:16.426
No, there's nothing warm
and fuzzy about this, Julia.

34:16.596 --> 34:19.588
And we need to tell someone
about them.

34:22.394 --> 34:24.385
Big Jim's gonna know what to do.

34:24.563 --> 34:28.932
Do you have any idea what will happen
if word gets out about those kids?

34:30.026 --> 34:31.766
The whole town will be after them.

34:33.113 --> 34:36.105
Until we know what this is,
we can't tell anyone.

34:41.288 --> 34:43.028
Fine.

34:44.624 --> 34:46.239
For now.

34:46.418 --> 34:48.409
[ALL CHATTERING]

35:18.033 --> 35:22.151
CAROLYN: I don't know
how you guys came up with this,

35:23.496 --> 35:25.873
but I'm glad you did.

35:28.043 --> 35:30.830
When She needs her next dose?

35:33.298 --> 35:37.337
Let's just be happy
she's better for now.

35:37.510 --> 35:39.341
Okay.

36:01.534 --> 36:02.865
[HORN HONKS]

36:05.497 --> 36:09.957
JULIA:
Barbie, I've been looking for you.

36:10.585 --> 36:12.496
You okay?

36:13.546 --> 36:15.207
BARBIE:
Yeah.

36:15.382 --> 36:17.623
You okay?

36:17.801 --> 36:20.042
JULIA:
Yeah, it's, uh...

36:21.262 --> 36:23.048
It's been a hell of a crazy day.

36:23.223 --> 36:26.386
Yeah, I guess you could say
everybody went a little crazy today.

36:34.859 --> 36:36.440
We're gonna be Okay.

37:15.650 --> 37:17.561
Hello?

37:17.736 --> 37:20.102
JIM:
I'd take it easy if I were you.

37:21.406 --> 37:22.646
[ANGIE GROANING]

37:24.743 --> 37:26.404
What...?

37:27.829 --> 37:29.694
What is going on?

37:29.873 --> 37:32.580
Barbie found you knocked out
in the diner.

37:32.751 --> 37:34.616
Rose.

37:36.045 --> 37:37.785
She needs help.

37:38.548 --> 37:40.914
I'm afraid it'S too late.

37:47.015 --> 37:49.347
She was a good friend to me.

37:55.565 --> 37:57.305
What...?

37:58.318 --> 38:00.809
What am I doing here?

38:02.489 --> 38:04.605
You can't lock me up again.

38:04.783 --> 38:07.274
No, no, the front door's Open.
You can leave any time you like.

38:09.704 --> 38:12.821
Though I was hoping

38:12.999 --> 38:17.459
that you and I could
come to an arrangement.

38:21.341 --> 38:24.333
Junior kidnapped me.

38:24.511 --> 38:26.126
No amount of money
can pay for that.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.636
You'll get no argument from me.

38:30.308 --> 38:32.469
You know, deep down,

38:33.186 --> 38:38.101
I think I always knew
something was off with my son,

38:38.983 --> 38:41.360
ever Since his mom died.

38:42.695 --> 38:46.688
I guess I just couldn't admit it
to myself.

38:48.743 --> 38:52.702
So I'm not talking
about giving you money.

38:53.665 --> 38:56.532
I'm Offering you my word.

38:57.752 --> 38:58.867
Your word?

38:59.045 --> 39:02.708
Junior Rennie will never touch you
again. I'll make sure of it.

39:05.885 --> 39:11.505
And, uh, well, I mean,
if you need money,

39:11.683 --> 39:15.926
or what counts as money
in town these days,

39:16.104 --> 39:22.395
you know, propane, food,
water, a gun,

39:23.903 --> 39:25.859
you1lhaveit

39:26.614 --> 39:32.325
If you will just try to put
this terrible event behind you,

39:34.038 --> 39:39.283
I'll get you anything
your little heart desires.

39:42.213 --> 39:43.919
What about Joe?

39:44.090 --> 39:46.923
I need to know that my brother
will be taken care of too.

39:47.760 --> 39:48.795
Done.

39:50.930 --> 39:52.841
We can be friends.

39:55.435 --> 39:57.426
And, uh...

39:58.521 --> 40:02.685
Trust me, times like these,

40:03.276 --> 40:04.891
it's good to have a friend like--

40:05.069 --> 40:06.775
Big Jim Rennie.

40:09.365 --> 40:10.775
I don't know.

40:12.285 --> 40:13.616
I have to think about it.

40:13.786 --> 40:16.072
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

40:16.247 --> 40:17.828
Dad.

40:21.127 --> 40:22.742
Angie.

40:25.465 --> 40:27.626
What's going on here?
